<paragraph blockId="15.[151,684,477,780]" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">
<taxonomicName box="[177,372,477,504]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ehretiaceae" genus="Ehretia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="15" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meyersii">
<emphasis box="[177,372,477,504]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">Ehretia meyersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation collectionCode="M" country="Madagascar" county="Daraina" location="Malagasy" municipality="David" pageId="15" pageNumber="152" specimenCount="1">
is distinctive among the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7F795138FFB9FFAFFD2DFDBBA91DFAFE:F20FB6F5FFBBFFAFFF70FE11A892FDDB" box="[151,251,509,535]" country="Madagascar" county="Daraina" municipality="David" name="Malagasy" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">Malagasy</location>
species in its rather large leaves (4-8.5 × 
<quantity box="[151,252,538,565]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="152" unit="cm" value="3.75" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5-5 cm</quantity>
) that are widest above the middle. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7F795138FFB9FFAFFD2DFDBBA91DFAFE:F20FB6F5FFBBFFAFFD66FDF6AAFBFDF8" box="[641,658,538,564]" country="Madagascar" county="Daraina" municipality="David" name="It" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">It</location>
is known from only two dry forest sites in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,285,601,627]" name="Madagascar" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, while most of the other 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7F795138FFB9FFAFFD2DFDBBA91DFAFE:F20FB6F5FFBBFFAFFDA3FDB5AAC5FDBF" box="[580,684,601,627]" country="Madagascar" county="Daraina" municipality="David" name="Malagasy" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">Malagasy</location>
species occur in dry forests in the south. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ehretiaceae" genus="Ehretia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="15" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meyersii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">Ehretia meyersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named in honor of 
<collectingMunicipality box="[477,544,662,688]" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">David</collectingMunicipality>
<collectionCode box="[551,580,661,687]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15637" name="Botanische Staatssammlung München" pageId="15" pageNumber="152" type="Herbarium">M</collectionCode>
. MEYERS, who collected plant specimens in poorly explored forests of northern 
<collectingCountry box="[380,515,723,749]" name="Madagascar" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
near 
<collectingCounty box="[583,679,723,749]" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">Daraina</collectingCounty>
, including the 
<typeStatus box="[302,348,753,779]" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">type</typeStatus>
of this species
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
