<paragraph blockId="15.[151,684,814,1148]" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">
CONSERVATION STATUS. — Provisional IUCN Red List Category: Endangered (EN B1abiiv+B2abi-iv). With an Extent of occurrence of 400 sq. km. and an Area of Occupancy of only 300 sq. km. 
<taxonomicName box="[291,458,1060,1087]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ehretiaceae" genus="Ehretia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="15" pageNumber="152" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meyersii">
<emphasis box="[291,458,1060,1087]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">Ehretia meyersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from dry forests in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[424,559,1091,1117]" name="Madagascar" pageId="15" pageNumber="152">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, which are quite small and not currently protected.
